==Abstract==

This IIP specifies invoice encoding for Lightning payments, adapted from BOLT #11.

==Specification==

===Invoice Format===

Invoices are Bech32-encoded with human-readable prefix:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Network !! Prefix
|-
| Mainnet || int
|-
| Testnet || tint
|}

Example: int1qp...xyz

===Invoice Fields===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Tag !! Description
|-
| p || Payment hash (52 chars)
|-
| d || Description
|-
| n || Payee node ID
|-
| h || Description hash (for long descriptions)
|-
| x || Expiry time in seconds
|-
| c || CLTV expiry delta
|-
| f || Fallback on-chain address
|-
| r || Routing hints
|}

===Amount Encoding===

Amounts use multiplier suffixes:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Suffix !! Multiplier
|-
| m || milli-INT (1/1,000)
|-
| u || micro-INT (1/1,000,000)
|-
| n || nano-INT (1/1,000,000,000)
|-
| p || pico-INT (1/1,000,000,000,000)
|}

Example: int100m... = 100 milli-INT = 0.1 INT

===Signature===

Invoices are signed with the payee's node key (ML-DSA-87):
<pre>
signature = Sign(recovery_flag || SHA3_256(hrp || data))
</pre>

Signature is appended to the invoice data.

===Routing Hints===

For private channels, include routing hints:
<pre>
pubkey || short_channel_id || fee_base_mint || fee_proportional || cltv_delta
</pre>

